			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Taresar is right. When you give yourself a shielding spell it looks like your HP goes down, what is really happening is your max HP goes up. 160/160 HP is a full bar, but you look like you're injured after spell casting when you suddenly have 160/176. This increases max HP on your pet, which also helps explain the longer regen time.
			</font>
	
